-- India Company Law Board sees Satyam approval soon
-- 
-- Mon Apr 13, 2009 3:08am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/04/13/us-satyam-companylaw-sb-idUSTRE53C0V020090413

 

 NEW DELHI  (Reuters) - India's company law board expects fraud-hit Satyam Computer Services SATY.BO to file for approval of the winning bidder within 2-3 days, its chairman said on Monday. 

 The approval should not take more than 24 hours after filing, S. Balasubramanian told reporters. Satyam said Indian IT services firm Tech Mahindra ( TEML.BO ) was the wining bidder with an offer of 58 rupees a share. (Reporting by  Devidutta Tripathy ; Editing by  John Mair )